      "content": "Thanks for the draft. It's a good start, but honestly, mentioning \"ten subjects\" and calling it a \"pilot study\" in the abstract might be a death sentence for a Nature submission. They look for massive, robust data sets. Can we rephrase the methodology section of the abstract to better emphasize the scale and statistical weight of the study without actually changing the data? I want to make sure the peer reviewers see the robustness of the findings immediately.",
